LGPL-2.1 Compliance Notice (OpenCASCADE Technology):

The OCCT component is dynamically loaded at runtime as a separate Web Worker
(bitbybit-dev-occt-webworker.js) and WebAssembly binary
(bitbybit-dev-occt.*.wasm). These files are NOT compiled into the Runner
bundle. Per LGPL-2.1 Section 6, you may replace the OCCT worker and WASM
with your own modified version by:

  1. Compiling your modified OpenCASCADE source to WebAssembly.
  2. Creating a Web Worker that implements the same message protocol
     (see documentation: https://bitbybit.dev/learn/runners/worker-protocol).
  3. Hosting your custom worker and WASM files on your own server.
  4. Using the cdnUrl option when initializing the runner:
     runner.run({ cdnUrl: 'https://your-server.com/assets/' })

The OpenCASCADE source code is publicly available at:
https://dev.opencascade.org/

